The paper introduces a new family of filtrations for Topological Data Analysis that is more robust to noise and outliers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category, which deals with the design and analysis of algorithms for geometric problems. Additionally, the paper relies on the notion of distance-to-measure functions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category, which deals with the design and analysis of efficient algorithms and data structures for computational problems. The paper also discusses the approximation of distance-to-measure functions, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category, which deals with the design and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. The paper also presents numerical experiments, which suggests that it may belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category, which deals with the design and analysis of numerical algorithms for solving mathematical problems. Finally, the paper deals with the robustness of Topological Data Analysis methods, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category, which deals with the analysis of social and information networks using computational methods.
